<div id="review_441691063" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/441691063" />
    <a title="Kathleen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13954899-kathleen"><img alt="Kathleen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1365166675p2/13954899.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/441691063?book_show_action=true">Oct 25, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kathleen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kathleen" href="/user/show/13954899-kathleen">Kathleen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13954899-kathleen?shelf=humorous">humorous</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13954899-kathleen?shelf=series-opener">series-opener</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13954899-kathleen?shelf=regency">regency</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13954899-kathleen?shelf=romance-historic">romance-historic</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer441691063" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10596584717973398251"><b>4.5 stars.<br/><br/> This heroine eats shoots and leaves. </b> A dark plot involving a sociopathic aunt and a heinous father, but also smexy-hot and highly entertaining. Absolutely one of the funniest historical romances I have read, with all the language and culture differences between Christina, raised among the Dakota tribe, and Lyon, raised to become a wealthy English Marquess. What a drool-worthy warrior spy. Tender, protective, and passionate. Good sense of humor, too. I want a Lyon of my own! <br/><br/>This is m</span>
  <span id="freeText10596584717973398251" style="display:none"><b>4.5 stars.<br /><br /> This heroine eats shoots and leaves. </b> A dark plot involving a sociopathic aunt and a heinous father, but also smexy-hot and highly entertaining. Absolutely one of the funniest historical romances I have read, with all the language and culture differences between Christina, raised among the Dakota tribe, and Lyon, raised to become a wealthy English Marquess. What a drool-worthy warrior spy. Tender, protective, and passionate. Good sense of humor, too. I want a Lyon of my own! <br /><br />This is my favorite of the Crown Spies series, along with <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/107781.The_Gift__Crown_s_Spies___3_" title="The Gift (Crown's Spies, #3) by Julie Garwood" rel="nofollow noopener">The Gift</a>. Some funny scenes below. <blockquote>Scene 1, under attack: <br /><i>"Christina had to run to keep up with Lyon. "I haven't braided my hair," she said quickly. '"I really must Lyon. It could be used against me. Surely you realize that?'"<br /><br />He didn't realize, knew he shouldn't ask, but did anyway. "Why is your hair a weapon?"<br /><br />"The men could catch hold of me if they grab my hair. Unless, of course, I'm quick as a panther, fearless as a wolf, and cunning as a bear!"<br /><br />The woman was getting carried away. Lyon let her see his exasperation...</i></blockquote> And many more chuckle-worthy scenes. The Summertons. The elderly decrepit butler. Putting out his shoes. Eating leaves. Etc. etc. <blockquote> Scene 2, departing the reception for the wedding night:<i><br /><br />Aunt Harriott looked at Lyon. "Be gentle this night," she instructed Lyon. <br /><br />"I shall." It was Christina who gave the promise. <br /><br />Both Lyon and his aunt looked at her. "She means me, Christina," Lyon said dryly.</i></blockquote><br /><b>Content:</b> At least three explicit sex scenes. Mild cussing, just a little. No profanity. Mild violence with a fight scene, but old diary and old war records describe grizzly murder scenes.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10596584717973398251" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

