        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer51311831" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13180299545179157596">&quot;The chaos surrounding her was confusing. Everyone was suddenly talking at the same time. Perhaps she should try to swoon after all, Christina considered. No, the settee was already taken, and the floor didn&apos;t look all that appealing. She settled on wringing her hands. It was the best she could do to look upset.&quot; <br/><br/>The first book in the <i>Crown&apos;s Spies</i> series. Julie Garwood writes some of the best heroes in the business in my humble opinion. Lyon, Marquess of Lyonwood, has met his match in Christina</span>
  <span id="freeText13180299545179157596" style="display:none">"The chaos surrounding her was confusing. Everyone was suddenly talking at the same time. Perhaps she should try to swoon after all, Christina considered. No, the settee was already taken, and the floor didn't look all that appealing. She settled on wringing her hands. It was the best she could do to look upset." <br /><br />The first book in the <i>Crown's Spies</i> series. Julie Garwood writes some of the best heroes in the business in my humble opinion. Lyon, Marquess of Lyonwood, has met his match in Christina, the mysterious princess. Christina is a wonderful heroine. She had a much different upbringing than the young women of the <i>ton</i>. Lyon has decided to discover all the secrets of the beautiful princess. Such a fun read full of witty banter. Lyon is my favorite type of hero. An uber-alpha with a protective side. I didn't think he was really portrayed quite as scary and dangerous as Ms Garwood wanted the readers to believe but still I loved him.</span>
