  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1402254578" />
    <a title="KatieV" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18620847-katiev"><img alt="KatieV" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1390618322p2/18620847.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1402254578?book_show_action=true">Sep 27, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="KatieV" class="user" itemprop="url" name="KatieV" href="/user/show/18620847-katiev">KatieV</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook 9781469261331" href="/book/show/15949918-the-lion-s-lady">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18620847-katiev?shelf=audiobook">audiobook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18620847-katiev?shelf=hero-dominate-alpha">hero-dominate-alpha</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18620847-katiev?shelf=genre-historical">genre-historical</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18620847-katiev?shelf=hero-warrior-soldier">hero-warrior-soldier</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18620847-katiev?shelf=heroine-virgin">heroine-virgin</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18620847-katiev?shelf=hero-titled">hero-titled</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18620847-katiev?shelf=locale-england">locale-england</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18620847-katiev?shelf=mistaken-secret-identity">mistaken-secret-identity</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1402254578" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14014336105760782556">This was a great light, feel-good listen. Great for when you just want something to put a smile on your face (like most Julie Garwood&apos;s). The narrator, Susan Duerden really brings the story alive. <br/><br/>This is a fish out of water story and parts of it were quite amusing. The increasingly ridiculous lies the heroine tells the hero to hide her true identity are pretty funny. <br/><br/>The heroine was a white girl raised by Dakota Indians who has taken her place in the Ton to try and fulfill her deceased mother&apos;s</span>
  <span id="freeText14014336105760782556" style="display:none">This was a great light, feel-good listen. Great for when you just want something to put a smile on your face (like most Julie Garwood's). The narrator, Susan Duerden really brings the story alive. <br /><br />This is a fish out of water story and parts of it were quite amusing. The increasingly ridiculous lies the heroine tells the hero to hide her true identity are pretty funny. <br /><br />The heroine was a white girl raised by Dakota Indians who has taken her place in the Ton to try and fulfill her deceased mother's wishes and bring justice to her evil father. The hero is a Marquess and former soldier in the Napoleonic wars. Likely quite light on historical/cultural accuracy, but entertaining all the same.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14014336105760782556" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
